The paper deals with the Feedback Vertex Set problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The algorithms presented in the paper are based on techniques from parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that studies the complexity of problems with respect to some measure of input size beyond the standard input size (e.g., the size of a solution). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are those related to algorithms and complexity theory, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
